ce reverberated throughout the rest of the fruit's production system. The particular conditions of plants, soils, chemicals, climate, and laboring bodies that once made strawberry production so lucrative in the Golden State have now changed and become a set of related threats that jeopardize the future of the industry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aSoilborne plant pathogensxControl. 0aStrawberriesxDiseases and pestsxControl. 0aStrawberry industryzCalifornia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  abackbreaking labor conditions.  acalifornia.  acontrol fungal pathogens.  adependence on toxic soil fumigants.  ajeopardize future of industry.  alucrative.  anations favorite berry.  aproduces eighty eight percent.  arely on soil fumigants.  arest of fruits production system.  asixth highest grossing crop.  astory of strawberry industry.  astrawberries in california.  astrawberries.  astrawberry production in golden state.  athought provoking.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520973343zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn